{"word": "about", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adverb", "meaning": {"english": "approximately; used to show that something is not exact", "chinese": "大约；用于表示某事物不精确"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "It's about 5 o'clock.", "chinese": "大约是5点钟。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "preposition", "meaning": {"english": "used to show movement within an area", "chinese": "用于表示在某区域内移动"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She walked about the park.", "chinese": "她在公园里走来走去。"}]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "above", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "preposition", "meaning": {"english": "in or to a higher position than", "chinese": "在…上方"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The plane flew above the clouds.", "chinese": "飞机在云层上方飞行。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "adverb", "meaning": {"english": "in or to a higher position", "chinese": "在上面"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The stars were shining brightly above.", "chinese": "星星在上面闪烁。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "greater in number, amount, or degree", "chinese": "更多的，更大的"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The temperature was above average.", "chinese": "温度高于平均水平。"}]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "across", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adverb", "meaning": {"english": "from one side to the other of something with clear limits, such as an area of land, a road, or a river", "chinese": "从一边到另一边，横过"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He walked across the street.", "chinese": "他走过马路。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "preposition", "meaning": {"english": "from one side to the other of something with clear limits, such as an area of land, a road, or a river", "chinese": "从一边到另一边，横过"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She swam across the river.", "chinese": "她游过河。"}]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "action", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The process of doing something, typically to achieve an aim.", "chinese": "行动，行为，活动"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She took action to solve the problem.", "chinese": "她采取行动来解决问题。"}], "synonyms": ["activity", "deed"], "antonyms": ["inaction"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "action", "plural": "actions"}}}

{"word": "activity", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The state of being active or the amount of activity involved in a particular area or thing.", "chinese": "活动的状态或特定领域或事物中的活动量。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The school offers a variety of activities for students.", "chinese": "学校为学生提供各种活动。"}, {"english": "There was a lot of activity in the park today.", "chinese": "今天公园里有很多活动。"}], "synonyms": ["action", "movement"], "antonyms": ["inactivity", "rest"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "activity", "plural": "activities"}}}

{"word": "actor", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a person who performs in plays, films, or television", "chinese": "演员"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She is a famous actor.", "chinese": "她是一位著名的演员。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "actor", "plural": "actors"}}}

{"word": "add", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to put something with another thing in order to increase the size, number, amount, etc.", "chinese": "添加；增加"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Please add some sugar to the tea.", "chinese": "请在茶里加些糖。"}, {"english": "If you add 2 and 3, you get 5.", "chinese": "如果你把2和3相加，你会得到5。"}], "synonyms": ["increase", "include"], "antonyms": ["subtract", "remove"]}], "forms": {"verb": {"base_form": "add", "third_person_singular": "adds", "past_tense": "added", "past_participle": "added", "present_participle": "adding"}}}

{"word": "afraid", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "Feeling fear or anxiety; frightened.", "chinese": "感到害怕或焦虑的；恐惧的。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She was afraid of the dark.", "chinese": "她害怕黑暗。"}, {"english": "He felt afraid when he saw the big dog.", "chinese": "他看到那只大狗时感到害怕。"}], "synonyms": ["scared", "frightened"], "antonyms": ["brave", "fearless"]}]}

{"word": "after", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "preposition", "meaning": {"english": "later than a particular time", "chinese": "在……之后"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "We will eat dinner after 7 o'clock.", "chinese": "我们将在7点之后吃晚饭。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "conjunction", "meaning": {"english": "following a particular time", "chinese": "在……之后"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "After you finish your homework, you can play.", "chinese": "你完成作业后，就可以玩了。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "adverb", "meaning": {"english": "later", "chinese": "后来"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I saw him again after a few days.", "chinese": "几天后我又见到了他。"}]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "afternoon", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The time from noon or lunchtime until evening", "chinese": "下午，午后"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "We will meet in the afternoon.", "chinese": "我们下午见面。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "afternoon", "plural": "afternoons"}}}

{"word": "age", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The length of time that a person has lived or a thing has existed.", "chinese": "年龄；寿命"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She is 10 years old.", "chinese": "她10岁了。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To grow old or cause something to grow old.", "chinese": "变老；使……变老"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Time ages everyone.", "chinese": "时间使人变老。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "age", "plural": "ages"}, "verb": {"base_form": "age", "third_person_singular": "ages", "past_tense": "aged", "past_participle": "aged", "present_participle": "aging"}}}

{"word": "air", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The invisible mixture of gases that surrounds the Earth and that we breathe.", "chinese": "空气，大气"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "We need air to breathe.", "chinese": "我们需要空气来呼吸。"}], "synonyms": ["atmosphere", "oxygen"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To let fresh air into a room by opening a window or door.", "chinese": "通风，换气"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She aired the room by opening the window.", "chinese": "她打开窗户给房间通风。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "air", "plural": "airs"}, "verb": {"base_form": "air", "third_person_singular": "airs", "past_tense": "aired", "past_participle": "aired", "present_participle": "airing"}}}

{"word": "airport", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A place where airplanes take off and land, and where passengers and cargo are handled.", "chinese": "机场，飞机起飞和降落的地方，以及处理乘客和货物的地方。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "We arrived at the airport early.", "chinese": "我们早早地到达了机场。"}, {"english": "The airport is very busy today.", "chinese": "今天机场非常繁忙。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "airport", "plural": "airports"}}}

{"word": "amazing", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "very surprising or impressive", "chinese": "令人惊讶或印象深刻的"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The movie was amazing.", "chinese": "这部电影非常棒。"}, {"english": "She has an amazing talent for drawing.", "chinese": "她在绘画方面有惊人的天赋。"}], "synonyms": ["astonishing", "incredible"], "antonyms": ["ordinary", "common"]}]}

{"word": "answer", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A reply or response to a question, statement, or request.", "chinese": "对问题、陈述或请求的回复或响应。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She gave a quick answer to the teacher's question.", "chinese": "她很快回答了老师的问题。"}], "synonyms": ["reply", "response"], "antonyms": ["question", "inquiry"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To say or write something in response to a question, statement, or request.", "chinese": "对问题、陈述或请求进行口头或书面回应。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He answered the phone when it rang.", "chinese": "电话响时他接了电话。"}], "synonyms": ["respond", "reply"], "antonyms": ["ignore", "refuse"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "answer", "plural": "answers"}, "verb": {"base_form": "answer", "third_person_singular": "answers", "past_tense": "answered", "past_participle": "answered", "present_participle": "answering"}}}

{"word": "any", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "used to refer to one or some of a thing or number of things, no matter how much or how many", "chinese": "用于指代一件事或一些事，无论多少"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Do you have any questions?", "chinese": "你有什么问题吗？"}], "synonyms": ["some"], "antonyms": ["none"]}, {"part_of_speech": "pronoun", "meaning": {"english": "used to refer to one or more people or things from a definite set of people or things", "chinese": "用于指代一组明确的人或事物中的一个或多个"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Choose any book you like.", "chinese": "选择你喜欢的任何一本书。"}]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "apple", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A round fruit with red, yellow, or green skin and a white inside.", "chinese": "一种圆形水果，有红色、黄色或绿色的皮，里面是白色的。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I ate an apple for breakfast.", "chinese": "我早餐吃了一个苹果。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "apple", "plural": "apples"}}}

{"word": "April", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The fourth month of the year", "chinese": "一年中的第四个月"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "My birthday is in April.", "chinese": "我的生日在四月。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "April"}}}

{"word": "arm", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "one of the two upper limbs of the human body from the shoulder to the hand", "chinese": "手臂"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She waved her arm to say goodbye.", "chinese": "她挥动手臂说再见。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to equip with weapons", "chinese": "武装"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The soldiers were armed with guns.", "chinese": "士兵们配备了枪支。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "arm", "plural": "arms"}, "verb": {"base_form": "arm", "third_person_singular": "arms", "past_tense": "armed", "past_participle": "armed", "present_participle": "arming"}}}

{"word": "pay", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To give money to someone for goods or services.", "chinese": "为商品或服务向某人付款。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I need to pay for the groceries.", "chinese": "我需要为杂货付款。"}], "synonyms": ["remunerate", "compensate"], "antonyms": ["receive", "get"]}, {"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The money that is paid for work or a service.", "chinese": "为工作或服务支付的金钱。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She received her pay yesterday.", "chinese": "她昨天收到了工资。"}], "synonyms": ["wages", "salary"], "antonyms": ["expense", "cost"]}], "forms": {"verb": {"base_form": "pay", "third_person_singular": "pays", "past_tense": "paid", "past_participle": "paid", "present_participle": "paying"}, "noun": {"singular": "pay", "plural": "pays"}}}

{"word": "pen", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a tool used for writing or drawing with ink", "chinese": "钢笔；笔"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She picked up a pen and started writing.", "chinese": "她拿起一支笔开始写字。"}], "synonyms": ["quill", "fountain pen"], "antonyms": ["eraser"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to write or draw with a pen", "chinese": "用笔写或画"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He penned a letter to his friend.", "chinese": "他用笔给朋友写了一封信。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "pen", "plural": "pens"}, "verb": {"base_form": "pen", "third_person_singular": "pens", "past_tense": "penned", "past_participle": "penned", "present_participle": "penning"}}}

{"word": "pencil", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A thin stick of graphite or a similar substance, typically encased in a thin wood cylinder, used for writing or drawing.", "chinese": "铅笔，一种细长的石墨或类似物质的棒，通常包裹在薄木圆筒中，用于书写或绘画。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She picked up a pencil and started drawing.", "chinese": "她拿起一支铅笔开始画画。"}], "synonyms": ["pen", "crayon"], "antonyms": ["eraser"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "pencil", "plural": "pencils"}}}

{"word": "people", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "persons forming a group or assembly or associated under the same head or chief", "chinese": "人；人们"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Many people like to travel.", "chinese": "许多人喜欢旅行。"}], "synonyms": ["persons", "individuals"], "antonyms": ["nobody"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "person", "plural": "people"}}}

{"word": "pepper", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a powder made from dried berries of a bush, used to give a sharp taste to food", "chinese": "胡椒粉，由胡椒树的干浆果制成，用于给食物增添辛辣味道"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Add some pepper to the soup.", "chinese": "在汤里加一些胡椒粉。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to add a lot of small pieces of something to food", "chinese": "在食物中加入许多小颗粒的东西"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She peppered the salad with nuts.", "chinese": "她在沙拉里撒了些坚果。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "pepper", "plural": "peppers"}, "verb": {"base_form": "pepper", "third_person_singular": "peppers", "past_tense": "peppered", "past_participle": "peppered", "present_participle": "peppering"}}}

{"word": "perfect", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "Without any mistakes; correct in every way.", "chinese": "完美的；无瑕的；正确的"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She speaks perfect English.", "chinese": "她英语说得非常完美。"}], "synonyms": ["flawless", "ideal"], "antonyms": ["imperfect", "faulty"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To make something completely free from faults; to improve something until it is as good as possible.", "chinese": "使完美；使完善"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He practiced every day to perfect his piano skills.", "chinese": "他每天练习以完善他的钢琴技巧。"}]}], "forms": {"verb": {"base_form": "perfect", "third_person_singular": "perfects", "past_tense": "perfected", "past_participle": "perfected", "present_participle": "perfecting"}}}

{"word": "period", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a length of time", "chinese": "一段时间"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I studied for a long period.", "chinese": "我学习了很长一段时间。"}], "synonyms": ["time", "duration"], "antonyms": ["instant"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "period", "plural": "periods"}}}

{"word": "person", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a human being regarded as an individual", "chinese": "人，个体"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She is a very kind person.", "chinese": "她是一个非常善良的人。"}, {"english": "He is the first person to arrive.", "chinese": "他是第一个到达的人。"}], "synonyms": ["individual", "human"], "antonyms": ["group", "collective"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "person", "plural": "people"}}}

{"word": "personal", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "Concerning or belonging to a particular person rather than anyone else.", "chinese": "个人的；私人的"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "This is a personal matter and should not be discussed in public.", "chinese": "这是个人问题，不应该在公共场合讨论。"}], "synonyms": ["individual", "private"], "antonyms": ["public", "general"]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "phone", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A device used for talking to someone who is not in the same place as you.", "chinese": "电话，用于与不在同一地点的人通话的设备。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I called my friend on the phone.", "chinese": "我给朋友打了电话。"}], "synonyms": ["telephone"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To call someone using a phone.", "chinese": "打电话给某人。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She phoned me to say she was coming.", "chinese": "她打电话告诉我她要来了。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "phone", "plural": "phones"}, "verb": {"base_form": "phone", "third_person_singular": "phones", "past_tense": "phoned", "past_participle": "phoned", "present_participle": "phoning"}}}

{"word": "photograph", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a picture made using a camera", "chinese": "照片"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She took a photograph of the sunset.", "chinese": "她拍了一张日落的照片。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to take a picture of something or someone using a camera", "chinese": "拍照"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He likes to photograph birds.", "chinese": "他喜欢拍鸟的照片。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "photograph", "plural": "photographs"}, "verb": {"base_form": "photograph", "third_person_singular": "photographs", "past_tense": "photographed", "past_participle": "photographed", "present_participle": "photographing"}}}

{"word": "piano", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A large musical instrument with a keyboard, played by pressing black and white keys.", "chinese": "钢琴，一种大型键盘乐器，通过按下黑白键演奏。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She plays the piano very well.", "chinese": "她钢琴弹得很好。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "piano", "plural": "pianos"}}}

{"word": "picture", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A drawing, painting, or photograph of something or someone.", "chinese": "图画，绘画，照片"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She drew a picture of her cat.", "chinese": "她画了一幅她猫的图画。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "picture", "plural": "pictures"}}}

{"word": "place", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a particular position or area in space", "chinese": "地方；位置"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I left my keys in a safe place.", "chinese": "我把钥匙放在了一个安全的地方。"}], "synonyms": ["location", "spot"], "antonyms": ["nowhere"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to put something in a particular position", "chinese": "放置；安置"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Please place the book on the table.", "chinese": "请把书放在桌子上。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "place", "plural": "places"}, "verb": {"base_form": "place", "third_person_singular": "places", "past_tense": "placed", "past_participle": "placed", "present_participle": "placing"}}}

{"word": "plane", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a flat surface on which a straight line joining any two points on it would wholly lie", "chinese": "平面；水平面"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The tabletop is a plane.", "chinese": "桌面是一个平面。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a powered flying vehicle with fixed wings and a weight greater than that of the air it displaces", "chinese": "飞机"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He took a plane to New York.", "chinese": "他乘飞机去了纽约。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "plane", "plural": "planes"}}}

{"word": "play", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To engage in an activity for enjoyment and recreation rather than a serious or practical purpose.", "chinese": "进行娱乐或休闲活动，而不是为了严肃或实际的目的。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The children are playing in the park.", "chinese": "孩子们在公园里玩耍。"}], "synonyms": ["have fun", "enjoy"], "antonyms": ["work", "study"]}, {"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "An activity done for enjoyment and recreation, especially among children.", "chinese": "为了娱乐和休闲而进行的活动，尤其是孩子们的活动。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The children love their playtime.", "chinese": "孩子们喜欢他们的游戏时间。"}], "synonyms": ["game", "recreation"]}], "forms": {"verb": {"base_form": "play", "third_person_singular": "plays", "past_tense": "played", "past_participle": "played", "present_participle": "playing"}, "noun": {"singular": "play", "plural": "plays"}}}

{"word": "player", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A person who plays a game or sport, or who performs in a game, competition, or sport.", "chinese": "运动员；选手；比赛者"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He is a good football player.", "chinese": "他是一名优秀的足球运动员。"}, {"english": "The tennis player won the match.", "chinese": "那位网球选手赢得了比赛。"}], "synonyms": ["athlete", "competitor"], "antonyms": ["spectator"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "player", "plural": "players"}}}

{"word": "point", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a sharp end", "chinese": "尖端"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The needle has a sharp point.", "chinese": "针有一个尖端。"}], "synonyms": ["tip", "end"], "antonyms": ["base", "beginning"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "to aim or direct something at a particular place or person", "chinese": "指向或对准某处或某人"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He pointed his finger at the map.", "chinese": "他用手指指向地图。"}], "synonyms": ["direct", "aim"], "antonyms": ["ignore", "miss"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "point", "plural": "points"}, "verb": {"base_form": "point", "third_person_singular": "points", "past_tense": "pointed", "past_participle": "pointed", "present_participle": "pointing"}}}

{"word": "police", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The official organization that is responsible for making sure people obey the law and for keeping public order.", "chinese": "警察；警方"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The police are looking for the thief.", "chinese": "警察正在寻找小偷。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To control or keep order in a particular area using the police.", "chinese": "维持治安；管辖"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The area is policed by local officers.", "chinese": "这个地区由当地警察管辖。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "police", "plural": "police"}, "verb": {"base_form": "police", "third_person_singular": "polices", "past_tense": "policed", "past_participle": "policed", "present_participle": "policing"}}}

{"word": "poor", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "adjective", "meaning": {"english": "having little money or few possessions", "chinese": "贫穷的，贫困的"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The poor family lived in a small house.", "chinese": "这个贫困的家庭住在一个小房子里。"}], "synonyms": ["needy", "impoverished"], "antonyms": ["rich", "wealthy"]}], "forms": {}}

{"word": "watch", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A small timepiece worn on a strap on the wrist or carried in a pocket.", "chinese": "手表，戴在手腕上或放在口袋里的小型计时器。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She looked at her watch to check the time.", "chinese": "她看了看手表，确认时间。"}], "synonyms": ["timepiece", "wristwatch"], "antonyms": ["ignore"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "Look at or observe attentively over a period of time.", "chinese": "观看，在一段时间内仔细观察或注视。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He watched the movie with great interest.", "chinese": "他饶有兴趣地观看了这部电影。"}], "synonyms": ["observe", "view"], "antonyms": ["ignore", "overlook"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "watch", "plural": "watches"}, "verb": {"base_form": "watch", "third_person_singular": "watches", "past_tense": "watched", "past_participle": "watched", "present_participle": "watching"}}}

{"word": "water", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A clear liquid, essential for life, that falls from the sky as rain and is found in rivers, lakes, and seas.", "chinese": "水，一种清澈的液体，是生命所必需的，从天空中以雨的形式落下，存在于河流、湖泊和海洋中。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "Please drink some water.", "chinese": "请喝点水。"}]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "To pour water on plants or soil to help them grow.", "chinese": "给植物或土壤浇水以帮助它们生长。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I need to water the flowers.", "chinese": "我需要给花浇水。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "water", "plural": "waters"}, "verb": {"base_form": "water", "third_person_singular": "waters", "past_tense": "watered", "past_participle": "watered", "present_participle": "watering"}}}

{"word": "way", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A method, style, or manner of doing something; a way of life.", "chinese": "方法，方式；生活方式"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "There are many ways to solve this problem.", "chinese": "有很多方法可以解决这个问题。"}, {"english": "She has a very healthy way of living.", "chinese": "她有一种非常健康的生活方式。"}], "synonyms": ["method", "manner", "approach"], "antonyms": ["inability", "disability"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "way", "plural": "ways"}}}

{"word": "wear", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "have (something) on your body as a piece of clothing, a decoration, etc.", "chinese": "穿；戴"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She wears a red dress.", "chinese": "她穿了一件红色的裙子。"}], "synonyms": ["dress in", "put on"], "antonyms": ["remove", "take off"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "have a particular expression on your face.", "chinese": "面带（某种表情）"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He wears a smile.", "chinese": "他面带微笑。"}]}], "forms": {"verb": {"base_form": "wear", "third_person_singular": "wears", "past_tense": "wore", "past_participle": "worn", "present_participle": "wearing"}}}

{"word": "weather", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The state of the atmosphere at a particular place and time, especially with reference to its effects on life and human activities.", "chinese": "天气，指某一地点在某一特定时间的大气状态，尤其是对生命和人类活动的影响。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The weather was nice today.", "chinese": "今天天气很好。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "weather", "plural": "weathers"}}}

{"word": "website", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "A collection of web pages and related content that is identified by a common domain name and published on at least one web server.", "chinese": "网站，指由网页及相关内容组成，通过一个共同的域名标识，并发布在一个或多个网络服务器上的集合。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "I found a lot of useful information on the company's website.", "chinese": "我在公司的网站上找到了很多有用的信息。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "website", "plural": "websites"}}}

{"word": "Wednesday", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "The fourth day of the week, coming after Tuesday and before Thursday.", "chinese": "一周的第四天，在星期二之后，星期四之前。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "We have a meeting every Wednesday.", "chinese": "我们每周三都有会议。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "Wednesday", "plural": "Wednesdays"}}}

{"word": "window", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "An opening in the wall of a building, vehicle, or container, which allows light and air to enter and can be closed by a windowpane or shutter.", "chinese": "建筑物、车辆或容器墙壁上的开口，允许光线和空气进入，可以用窗玻璃或百叶窗关闭。"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "She opened the window to let in some fresh air.", "chinese": "她打开窗户让新鲜空气进来。"}, {"english": "The cat jumped through the window.", "chinese": "猫从窗户跳了出去。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "window", "plural": "windows"}}}

{"word": "perspective", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "a particular attitude toward or way of regarding something; a point of view", "chinese": "观点；看法；视角"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "It's good to look at things from a different perspective.", "chinese": "从不同的角度看问题是有益的。"}]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "perspective", "plural": "perspectives"}}}

{"word": "wound", "definitions": [{"part_of_speech": "noun", "meaning": {"english": "An injury to living tissue caused by a cut, blow, or other impact, typically one in which the skin is cut or broken.", "chinese": "伤口，创伤"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "He had a deep wound on his arm.", "chinese": "他的手臂上有一个很深的伤口。"}], "synonyms": ["injury", "cut"], "antonyms": ["heal"]}, {"part_of_speech": "verb", "meaning": {"english": "Inflict an injury on (someone) by damaging the person's body.", "chinese": "使受伤，伤害"}, "example_sentences": [{"english": "The soldier was wounded in the battle.", "chinese": "士兵在战斗中受伤了。"}], "synonyms": ["injure", "harm"], "antonyms": ["heal", "cure"]}], "forms": {"noun": {"singular": "wound", "plural": "wounds"}, "verb": {"base_form": "wound", "third_person_singular": "wounds", "past_tense": "wounded", "past_participle": "wounded", "present_participle": "wounding"}}}
